    "top_event": "Helicopter slide off heliport into water",
    "incident_type": "Structural damage to crane/lifting device; required evacuation",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Helicopter floats deployed upon water contact",
      "Pilot evacuated to life raft",
      "M/V Miss Peggy Ann alerted and crew recovered pilot",
      "Helicopter monitored as it drifted with current",
      "Pilot underwent back surgery",
      "Pilot underwent physical therapy"
    ],
    "summary": "While at South Timbalier (ST) 127A platform, Island Operating Company employees noticed inclement weather developing. An RLC, LLC helicopter pilot was requested to transport operators to Ship Shoal (SS) 189B due to rough seas preventing crew boat transfer. During startup procedures, the helicopter slid off the south side of the heliport onto the water. The aircraft's floats deployed and the pilot evacuated to a life raft. The pilot sustained lower back injuries requiring surgery and subsequent physical therapy.",
